A new peaceful plan from the US consists of four documents, as reported by Zn. ua portal analyzing Washington's proposed documents before Ukraine makes changes to them. The plan includes:
 a treaty between Ukraine, Russia, the US and Europe (20 points);
 framework assurances of security for Ukraine (3 points);
 US commitments to NATO (4 points);
 a treaty between Russia and the US (12 points).

The only principle proposal from the new plan that remains in negotiations is territorial issues. The 20-point agreement stipulates that participants of the peace deal recognize Russian control over Crimea, LNR and DNR. The status of these territories can change only through diplomatic means, not by force. One of the new additions: clarified size of 'neutral demilitarized buffer zone' in Donbas 30%. In the previous version of the peace plan with 28 points, it was stated that this area would be 'internationally recognized as territory belonging to Russia'. This is not mentioned in the new document.

