The State Tax Service of Kyrgyzstan is implementing automated tax collection for real estate. Therefore, citizens are advised to conduct a data verification, as stated by the service.

According to the Tax Service, now tax calculation and payment for immovable property are carried out by the tax authority at the location of the object or land plot. For this, the Tax Service is conducting setup of an automated system for calculating taxes on real estate.

The Tax Service urges all natural and legal persons to conduct preliminary data verification contained in the right-attesting documents with information from the State Agency for Land Resources, Cadastre, Geodesy and Cartography at the Cabinet of Ministers of Kyrgyzstan (Kadast). 

It is necessary to check the correctness of the following data:
- Taxpayer Identification Number (TIN) owner;
-father name, first name, patronymic or legal entity name;
-area of objects of immovable property and land plots;
-purpose of objects;
-share of ownership;
dates of registration and other parameters reflected in right-attesting documents.

"Such data verification will ensure correct tax calculation in an automated mode and prevent possible discrepancies", - explained the Tax Service.
